one problem, your poll does not seperate different level ranges. <br>
in my experiance most low level druids (it should be noted that most druids in general are low level) are evocation specializied, whereas higher ones tend to be alteration. yes i do know there are still some high level evoc druids, but nearly all have learned by now that support is more valuable usually than offense and for this reason switch to alteration.<br>
<br>
its sort of how mages begin evocation and finish the game conjuration (weaker offense stronger support).<br>
<br>
why? because in the end we all learn that the best way to be effective is to either support melees or support other casters who are supporting melees. anyway, thats another topic (or rant maybe?). point is i <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> highly</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> doubt the primary spec for druids is 50/50 in upper levels. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=33330" target="new"><b>Noonie Violetskies</b>, 58 High Elven Conjurer</a> <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=61427" target="new"><b>Aylliah Ravenlure</b>, 45 Erudite Enchantress<br></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1668<br> <font color=#333399>(6/5/02 5:53:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27485.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upcoming changes to pets</span><hr size=1> <blockquote>yes i do know there are still some high level evoc druids, but nearly all have learned by now that support is more valuable usually than offense and for this reason switch to alteration.</blockquote><br>
